{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 170°C and line a large loaf tin (900 g\/2 lb) with baking paper.","Place almonds in mixing bowl and grind <b>5 sec\/speed 9<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place sugar and lemon peel in mixing bowl then grind <b>5 sec\/speed 10<b>."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Add butter and mix <b>2 min\/speed 3.5<b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add eggs, lemon juice and vanilla extract then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 3<b>.","Add flour, reserved ground almonds and milk then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 3.5<b>. Pour into prepared loaf tin and level the top. Bake for 30 minutes (170°C) then sprinkle candied peel over the centre of cake. Cover with foil then bake for a further 20-30 minutes (170°C) until a skewer inserted in centre comes out clean. Leave in tin to cool for 10 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely. Slice to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["55 g blanched almonds","170 g caster sugar","1 lemon, thin peelings of skin and juice","170 g unsalted butter, very soft","3 medium eggs","¼ tsp real vanilla extract","110 g self-raising flour","1 Tbsp milk","1 Tbsp candied lemon and orange peel, in small pieces"]}],"id":"r103891","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/--08iDN1dArk\/XZWqLurfcGI\/AAAAAAAAfUQ\/iIcxKXfgHYQVqUPEVOBiZjCmnmhwfivxwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_F83IVa9eBgUDvH5J.png","title":"Madeira Cake","publishedAt":"2016-07-11T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5.5 g","fat":"23.7 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"34.8 g","calories":"1565 kJ \/ 374 kcal"},"usefulItems":"900 g loaf tin (2 lb), wire rack, aluminium foil, oven","basicInfo":["easy","5m","1h 30m","8 slices"]}